creating blog instruction :

Phase one (settings project environment):
	1. creating main app for the whole django project 
	2. creating app for project and use it for deploying your project in your default web server
	4. creating urls in urls.py file from main app and include it with project app
	5. creating templates for running the project
	6. migrate database with default sqlite database or change database for postgremysql or mysql
		Here is the mysql setup code snippet. copy and paste it to settings.py file in main app

		MySql:
		DATABASES = {
		'default': {
		    'ENGINE': 'django.db.backends.mysql',
		    'NAME': 'database-name',
		    'HOST': '127.0.0.1',
		    'PORT': '3306',
		    'USER': 'root',  #user name
		    'PASSWORD': '',	 #password of user name
		}}

	7. install mysql client wtih command 'pip instlal mysqlclient' (only needed for mysql database)	
	8. add your ready app to INSTALLED_APPS list inside settigns file


Phase two (Migrate database):
	
	1.first write a model inside models.py file,Just like ..

		from django.db import models
		from django.contrib.auth.models import User
		from django.utils import timezone

		# Create your models here.


		class Post(models.Model):
		    title = models.CharField(max_length=100)
		    content = models.TextField(blank=True,null=True)
		    date_time = models.DateTimeField(default=timezone.now)
		    author = models.ForeignKey(User,on_delete=models.CASCADE)
		    class Meta:
		        db_table = 'post'


	2. migrate and add your newly write model into database with command like 'python3 manage.py makemigrations' 	        
	3. Then add it to database with this command line 'python3 manage.py migrate'
	
